	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=271291><span id= >Jrrazor</span></a><br><span id=notbold>6 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The smithing item that drops in Seru is a Belt that's 10% modifier to smithing, Massive girdle of the forge. It drops off one of the guild leaders (i don't remember his name). Below are the 3 items known to drop with a modifier to smithing(per EQ Traders corner):<br><br>Massive girdle of the forge (drop in Sanctus Seru): +10% smithing <br><br>Hammer of the ironfrost (drop off Xerkizh the Creator in Temple of Ssraeshza): +15% smithing <br><br>Gauntlets of dark embers (drop off Kaas Thox Xi Ans Dyex in Vex Thal): +15% smithing <br><br><br><br>Below is the posting from EQ Traders corner:<br><br>Q: If I have multiple enhancing items, does their effect stack or does it use the highest percentage one only? <br>A: According to the most recent communication with VI, the effects do NOT stack. Only the highest-bonus item of those you are wearing/wielding will apply. <br> <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue Nov&nbsp;&nbsp;4 16:14:51 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></td></tr>
